The paper discusses task planning algorithms for robotics, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence in robotics (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The comparison of PDDL and ASP as underlying action languages involves logical reasoning and programming, which could fall under the categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper also discusses the selection of general purpose planning systems, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
